## Type Checker Configuration

```toml
# pyproject.toml
[tool.ty]
python-version = "3.14"
error-on-warnings = true

[tool.ruff.lint]
select = [
    "TCH",    # TYPE_CHECKING imports
    "ANN",    # Missing type annotations
    "UP",     # pyupgrade — modern syntax
]
```

Run `ty check src/arvel/` in CI. Zero errors on the `data/` package is the baseline.

---

## Checklist (Before Merging)

- [ ] No new `Any` in public function signatures
- [ ] No new `dict[str, Any]` for structured data in public APIs
- [ ] No new `setattr` for typed attributes
- [ ] No new `cast` without a comment explaining the invariant
- [ ] No new `# type: ignore` without a comment explaining why
- [ ] `@overload` used when return type depends on input type
- [ ] `TypeGuard` used instead of `isinstance` + manual narrowing
- [ ] `Self` used on factory/constructor methods
- [ ] All re-exports use `X as X` pattern
- [ ] `ty check src/arvel/` passes with zero new errors
